1
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:09,744
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,290 --> 00:00:18,884
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,927 --> 00:00:22,088
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,764 --> 00:00:26,426
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,535 --> 00:00:30,163
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,872 --> 00:00:34,966
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,476 --> 00:00:38,741
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,214 --> 00:00:44,480
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,121 --> 00:00:48,986
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:50,819
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,891 --> 00:00:53,223
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,762 --> 00:00:56,525
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,597 --> 00:00:58,497
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,566 --> 00:01:01,000
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,903 --> 00:01:09,467
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,444 --> 00:01:13,072
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,514 --> 00:01:16,711
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,555 --> 00:01:22,920
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,326 --> 00:01:26,850
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:31,188 --> 00:01:33,315
You have to think when using Jutsu.

21
00:01:33,857 --> 00:01:36,018
They can be used against you.

22
00:01:37,761 --> 00:01:43,199
Also, don't get caught
in an obvious trap, you fool.

23
00:01:45,769 --> 00:01:47,930
A Ninja must see
through deception... got it?

24
00:01:48,338 --> 00:01:51,034
I know that!

25
00:01:51,508 --> 00:01:54,807
You know, you say that because
you <i>don't</i> get it. Listen up.

26
00:01:56,746 --> 00:01:59,112
Your movements are wasteful.

27
00:02:00,217 --> 00:02:00,740
<i>Now!</i>

28
00:02:04,888 --> 00:02:06,219
<i>He finally dropped his guard!</i>

29
00:02:07,023 --> 00:02:08,285
You're so...

30
00:02:12,262 --> 00:02:13,627
No way!

31
00:02:13,897 --> 00:02:16,388
You jerk Sasuke! You overdid it.

32
00:02:27,344 --> 00:02:29,335
<i>Damn! Another substitution?</i>

33
00:02:29,679 --> 00:02:32,079
<i>He must have found out my location</i>
<i>with those Shuriken!</i>

34
00:02:33,850 --> 00:02:36,683
<i>He purposely lowered his guard!</i>
<i>Serves me right...</i>

35
00:02:36,753 --> 00:02:38,084
<i>I fell for the trap.</i>

36
00:02:39,122 --> 00:02:40,282
So he's over there, eh...

37
00:02:43,226 --> 00:02:45,490
<i>Sasuke... Where are you?!</i>

38
00:02:46,496 --> 00:02:48,054
<i>Don't tell me,</i>
<i>Kakashi Sensei already...</i>

39
00:02:48,999 --> 00:02:49,624
<i>No!</i>

40
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,368
<i>That couldn't happen to Sasuke, right?!</i>

41
00:02:54,871 --> 00:02:56,839
<i>Safe! He didn't notice me.</i>

42
00:02:57,874 --> 00:02:59,341
Sakura, behind you.

43
00:02:59,409 --> 00:02:59,875
Huh?!

44
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:09,279
What's up with that "A Ninja must see
through deception" stuff?!

45
00:03:09,352 --> 00:03:13,083
Damn it! I'll never fall for his trap again!

46
00:03:19,029 --> 00:03:22,123
I fell for it again!

47
00:03:22,265 --> 00:03:28,204
<i>You Failed! Kakashi's Final Decision</i>

48
00:03:48,992 --> 00:03:51,017
What was that?! Huh?!

49
00:03:51,528 --> 00:03:53,462
Hold on! Where's Sensei?!

50
00:03:53,530 --> 00:03:54,963
Huh?! What's going on?!

51
00:03:55,632 --> 00:03:56,792
Huh?! What's what?!

52
00:03:57,901 --> 00:03:58,560
Sakura...

53
00:03:59,869 --> 00:04:00,597
Sasuke?!

54
00:04:02,105 --> 00:04:03,538
Sa... Saku... ra...

55
00:04:03,907 --> 00:04:06,205
P-Please... help... me...

56
00:04:17,354 --> 00:04:19,185
Maybe I went a bit overboard...

57
00:04:19,990 --> 00:04:22,982
But it's really something
she should notice...

58
00:04:24,327 --> 00:04:25,988
<i>Was that voice... Sakura's?</i>

59
00:04:26,997 --> 00:04:30,455
Shinobi Battle Skill #2, Genjutsu.

60
00:04:31,301 --> 00:04:33,792
Sakura was easily lured.

61
00:04:34,971 --> 00:04:36,097
<i>Genjutsu, huh...?</i>

62
00:04:36,272 --> 00:04:40,732
<i>An illusory mind controlling technique.</i>
<i>I'm not surprised she got lured.</i>

63
00:04:41,144 --> 00:04:41,701
<i>However...</i>

64
00:04:43,380 --> 00:04:45,541
I'm different from them.

65
00:04:46,416 --> 00:04:53,015
Why don't you say that after
you get a bell... Sasuke?

66
00:05:20,817 --> 00:05:23,081
It's no use just using
straightforward attacks.

67
00:05:26,523 --> 00:05:27,182
A trap?!

68
00:05:30,794 --> 00:05:31,385
<i>What?!</i>

69
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:45,640
<i>This guy's...?!</i>

70
00:05:52,816 --> 00:05:53,840
<i>What a guy.</i>

71
00:05:54,484 --> 00:05:56,645
<i>There's no time</i>
<i>to read "Make Out Paradise."</i>

72
00:06:01,157 --> 00:06:03,182
What?
I?!

73
00:06:06,129 --> 00:06:10,190
<i>That's right! I saw Sasuke on</i>
<i>the verge of dying and I...</i>

74
00:06:11,134 --> 00:06:14,035
Sasuke!
Don't die and leave me here!!

75
00:06:14,704 --> 00:06:16,035
Where are you?!

76
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:26,381
So that's what it looks like
behind the logs.

77
00:06:30,086 --> 00:06:33,249
Oh! There are box lunches on the stone!

78
00:06:34,691 --> 00:06:38,058
A Ninja must see through deception... eh?

79
00:06:41,898 --> 00:06:45,527
Well! I'll acknowledge that
you're different from those two.

80
00:06:48,838 --> 00:06:49,304
<i>Horse!</i>

81
00:06:50,340 --> 00:06:50,829
<i>Tiger!</i>

82
00:06:52,442 --> 00:06:54,273
<i>Fire Style! Fireball Jutsu!</i>

83
00:06:54,811 --> 00:06:57,644
What?! That's not a Jutsu
that a Genin can do...

84
00:06:58,248 --> 00:07:00,011
He shouldn't have
enough Chakra yet!

85
00:07:15,465 --> 00:07:18,593
<i>He's gone!</i>
<i>Is he behind me?! No, above me?!</i>

86
00:07:19,335 --> 00:07:20,131
Where is he?!

87
00:07:20,470 --> 00:07:21,061
I'm under you!!

88
00:07:24,407 --> 00:07:24,839
<i>Wha?!</i>

89
00:07:25,542 --> 00:07:27,942
Earth Style: Headhunter Jutsu.

90
00:07:35,385 --> 00:07:39,151
Shinobi Battle Skill #3, Ninjutsu.

91
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:42,524
How's that? You can't move, heh?

92
00:07:44,494 --> 00:07:49,261
Although, you're... already starting
to make your mark.

93
00:07:50,466 --> 00:07:51,364
But, oh well.

94
00:07:52,769 --> 00:07:55,670
They do say that the nail that sticks up
gets hammered down, so...

95
00:07:58,074 --> 00:07:58,631
Damn it!

96
00:08:02,278 --> 00:08:07,648
I don't have to naively take those bells.
I'll just eat in secret right now!

97
00:08:08,618 --> 00:08:10,449
Let's eat!!

98
00:08:10,587 --> 00:08:11,178
Hey.

99
00:08:13,556 --> 00:08:15,490
I was just joking...

100
00:08:15,725 --> 00:08:16,692
Too late!

101
00:08:17,727 --> 00:08:21,219
<i>Damn it! Is there this much of</i>
<i>a difference in strength?</i>

102
00:08:32,041 --> 00:08:32,803
Sakura...

103
00:08:34,978 --> 00:08:37,242
This time it's a freshly severed head?!

104
00:08:41,351 --> 00:08:42,909
What's up with her?

105
00:08:52,428 --> 00:08:53,360
Sasuke?

106
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:54,926
You're okay!

107
00:08:54,998 --> 00:08:56,727
Hey, cut it out!
Don't cling to me!

108
00:09:01,037 --> 00:09:04,404
There's not much time left until noon.
I'm going.

109
00:09:05,108 --> 00:09:07,906
Sasuke, you're still going
after the bells?!

110
00:09:08,945 --> 00:09:11,379
I was able to touch them last time.
Next time I'll be able to take them.

111
00:09:12,015 --> 00:09:14,449
What?!
I-I see.

112
00:09:14,917 --> 00:09:17,283
Sure enough,
you're awesome, Sasuke.

113
00:09:18,187 --> 00:09:21,816
There's no way I can take
the bells from Sensei.

114
00:09:22,258 --> 00:09:26,592
At this rate, I'll face
separation from Sasuke...

115
00:09:28,097 --> 00:09:31,692
Uh... say. There's really no time left...

116
00:09:32,201 --> 00:09:35,227
So let's just take it easy and
try again next time.

117
00:09:59,095 --> 00:10:02,622
I'm the only one
who can kill that man.

118
00:10:06,135 --> 00:10:10,902
Huh? What?
You mean Sensei?

119
00:10:12,275 --> 00:10:14,709
At that time... I was crying.

120
00:10:16,112 --> 00:10:17,010
Crying?

121
00:10:19,248 --> 00:10:20,010
My...

122
00:10:21,484 --> 00:10:23,952
What? What is it?

123
00:10:25,188 --> 00:10:29,750
I'm an avenger. I must become stronger
than that man...

124
00:10:30,293 --> 00:10:33,023
I don't have time for setbacks here...

125
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:40,659
<i>... to kill a certain man!</i>

126
00:10:43,406 --> 00:10:46,000
Damn it... I wasted my time talking.

127
00:10:48,111 --> 00:10:49,078
Sasuke...

128
00:10:57,854 --> 00:11:01,346
Oh oh, your stomachs are growling...

129
00:11:02,358 --> 00:11:04,918
By the way, about this exercise...

130
00:11:05,661 --> 00:11:09,597
Well! There's no need for you guys
to go back to the Academy.

131
00:11:12,168 --> 00:11:15,763
What? I... All I did was lay unconscious.

132
00:11:16,272 --> 00:11:17,534
Is that okay?

133
00:11:18,374 --> 00:11:20,842
Love is victorious!! Cha!!

134
00:11:23,112 --> 00:11:24,409
Yahooooo!

135
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:27,040
Then, then!
That means the three of us...

136
00:11:28,017 --> 00:11:29,678
Yes. The three of you...

137
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,548
must quit being Ninja!!

138
00:11:43,426 --> 00:11:44,950
N-No way!

139
00:11:45,862 --> 00:11:48,956
Kakashi hasn't passed
a single person this whole time...

140
00:11:49,566 --> 00:11:50,533
Iruka...

141
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:57,565
Even I don't know if it's good for
those kids to become Shinobi right away...

142
00:11:58,641 --> 00:12:02,042
However...
Kakashi's judgments were correct...

143
00:12:03,847 --> 00:12:06,714
Quit being Ninja?! What do you mean?!

144
00:12:06,883 --> 00:12:09,784
Uh, well it's true, we weren't able to
take the bells.

145
00:12:10,153 --> 00:12:13,145
But why do we have to be told to "quit"?!

146
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:18,190
That's because you're all squirts who
don't have the qualifications to become Ninja.

147
00:12:22,665 --> 00:12:23,222
Oh!

148
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:24,359
Sasuke!

149
00:12:25,902 --> 00:12:27,961
I'm saying you're squirts.

150
00:12:29,439 --> 00:12:31,930
Don't step on Sasuke!!

151
00:12:36,379 --> 00:12:39,906
Are you kids thinking that
being a Ninja is easy? Huh?

152
00:12:43,319 --> 00:12:47,756
Why do you think you're doing
this exercise in teams?

153
00:12:48,391 --> 00:12:49,983
Huh?! What do you mean?

154
00:12:50,693 --> 00:12:51,489
Put simply...

155
00:12:52,495 --> 00:12:55,760
it's as if you guys have no
understanding of the answer to this test.

156
00:12:56,466 --> 00:12:57,364
Answer?

157
00:12:58,401 --> 00:13:02,303
Yes. The answer that determines
passing or failing of this test.

158
00:13:02,972 --> 00:13:06,271
That's... what I've wanted to ask
about for a while now.

159
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:10,846
Man, are you guys brainless or what?

160
00:13:11,714 --> 00:13:14,512
Don't you get the meaning of
the three-man squad?!

161
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:19,411
Jeez!! What of three people to a squad?!

162
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:22,251
That's... teamwork!

163
00:13:24,027 --> 00:13:25,756
You mean, working together?

164
00:13:26,496 --> 00:13:30,091
Exactly. But it's too late even
if you realize that now.

165
00:13:30,967 --> 00:13:31,934
You might've been able to...

166
00:13:32,001 --> 00:13:34,629
take the bells if the three of you
had come at me...

167
00:13:35,305 --> 00:13:37,170
Well, it's too bad.

168
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:39,370
<i>Now wait a minute.</i>

169
00:13:39,876 --> 00:13:42,902
Why use teamwork if
there were only two bells?

170
00:13:43,012 --> 00:13:47,142
If the three of us were to desperately go
take the bells with one having to hold back,

171
00:13:47,217 --> 00:13:49,208
that wouldn't be teamwork.
That'd create internal discord.

172
00:13:49,686 --> 00:13:50,778
Of course!

173
00:13:51,521 --> 00:13:54,490
This is a test set up to purposely
place you against each other.

174
00:13:56,693 --> 00:14:00,459
It's under just such conditions
where one's own interests aren't the issue.

175
00:14:00,697 --> 00:14:05,157
The intention was to select those
who could prioritize teamwork...

176
00:14:06,269 --> 00:14:08,203
Despite this, you fools...

177
00:14:08,738 --> 00:14:09,397
Sakura!

178
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:13,776
You were only concerned with Sasuke and
you didn't even know where he was.

179
00:14:13,843 --> 00:14:16,175
And you didn't care for Naruto who was
right in front of your eyes...

180
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:17,905
Naruto!

181
00:14:18,882 --> 00:14:20,782
All you do is run solo...

182
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:27,249
You labeled the other two as hindrances
and acted on your own...

183
00:14:27,991 --> 00:14:29,618
Missions are carried out in squads!

184
00:14:30,126 --> 00:14:32,993
There's no mistaking that Ninjas need
unsurpassed individual skills...

185
00:14:33,329 --> 00:14:37,265
But "teamwork" is considered
more important than that.

186
00:14:38,134 --> 00:14:43,003
Individual actions that disrupt teamwork
throw the team into crisis and lead to death...

187
00:14:44,174 --> 00:14:45,106
For example...

188
00:14:46,543 --> 00:14:50,070
"Sakura! Kill Naruto, or else Sasuke dies..."

189
00:14:51,481 --> 00:14:53,506
What?! What?! Whaaat?!

190
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:55,842
Is what will... happen.

191
00:14:59,055 --> 00:15:00,886
Oh, I was so surpised.

192
00:15:02,992 --> 00:15:04,584
On top of having a hostage taken,

193
00:15:04,661 --> 00:15:07,289
you're faced with two impossible choices
and end up being killed.

194
00:15:09,132 --> 00:15:11,657
Every mission is
a life risking assignment.

195
00:15:15,438 --> 00:15:16,427
Look at this...

196
00:15:16,739 --> 00:15:19,674
The many names engraved
on this stone...

197
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:24,639
These are all Ninjas who are called
heroes in the village.

198
00:15:26,082 --> 00:15:29,381
That that that that! I like thaaat!

199
00:15:29,886 --> 00:15:33,083
I've decided now to get
my name engraved there, too!

200
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:37,319
A hero! A hero!
I'm not going to die like a dog!

201
00:15:38,962 --> 00:15:41,328
But... they're not just ordinary heroes.

202
00:15:41,698 --> 00:15:45,600
No kidding. Then, what kind
of heroes are they?

203
00:15:48,538 --> 00:15:49,971
Hey! Hey!

204
00:15:50,106 --> 00:15:51,937
They are heroes
who were killed in action.

205
00:15:53,409 --> 00:15:54,740
Killed in action?

206
00:15:55,345 --> 00:15:58,041
It means they died
performing a mission.

207
00:16:07,523 --> 00:16:08,751
This is a memorial.

208
00:16:09,292 --> 00:16:12,750
The names of my friends
are also engraved here...

209
00:16:25,942 --> 00:16:29,309
I'll give you guys one more chance!

210
00:16:29,946 --> 00:16:33,473
However, after noon it'll be
a harsher battle to take the bell.

211
00:16:34,450 --> 00:16:36,247
Those who want to take on
the challenge can eat lunch.

212
00:16:36,352 --> 00:16:38,752
However, don't let Naruto have any.

213
00:16:40,723 --> 00:16:43,954
It's punishment for breaking the rules and
attempting to eat lunch on your own.

214
00:16:45,028 --> 00:16:46,723
If someone lets him eat...

215
00:16:47,263 --> 00:16:49,356
that person will be disqualified
on the spot.

216
00:16:53,970 --> 00:16:57,269
<i>I make the rules, here. Got it?!</i>

217
00:16:59,509 --> 00:17:00,237
I must be going.

218
00:17:01,411 --> 00:17:02,844
Listen to me, Iruka.

219
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,312
What?

220
00:17:05,181 --> 00:17:08,810
No matter what the result,
don't hold it against Kakashi...

221
00:17:11,487 --> 00:17:12,078
Alright.

222
00:17:25,435 --> 00:17:31,135
I'm okay with not eating lunch!
No sweat at all!

223
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:34,708
No sweat...

224
00:17:40,383 --> 00:17:41,213
Here.

225
00:17:43,219 --> 00:17:47,212
H-Hey, Sasuke.
Sensei just said!

226
00:17:47,757 --> 00:17:51,022
It's okay.
There's no sign of him now.

227
00:17:51,527 --> 00:17:53,927
The three of us are going to go
take the bells together.

228
00:17:54,597 --> 00:17:57,691
It'll be trouble for me
if he becomes a hindrance, so...

229
00:17:59,068 --> 00:17:59,932
<i>Sasuke...</i>

230
00:18:11,514 --> 00:18:12,674
Sakura...

231
00:18:20,456 --> 00:18:21,548
Thanks...

232
00:18:22,425 --> 00:18:24,723
Don't thank me.
Just hurry up and eat.

233
00:18:25,294 --> 00:18:26,886
But...

234
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:31,260
I'm on... a diet...
I mean I just eat less than Sasuke.

235
00:18:31,801 --> 00:18:33,063
So you don't need to worry.

236
00:18:33,970 --> 00:18:35,062
But...

237
00:18:36,739 --> 00:18:37,262
See...

238
00:18:37,907 --> 00:18:38,805
Wha?!

239
00:18:39,475 --> 00:18:41,636
Hurry it up.
We don't know when he'll be back...

240
00:18:43,246 --> 00:18:44,907
It's just this one time.

241
00:18:44,981 --> 00:18:47,677
Okay? You got it?!

242
00:18:48,351 --> 00:18:50,148
I got it.

243
00:18:59,061 --> 00:19:00,585
You three!

244
00:19:00,830 --> 00:19:02,354
Yiiikes!

245
00:19:05,668 --> 00:19:09,263
You defied the rules so that
means you know what's coming...

246
00:19:15,344 --> 00:19:17,107
Do you have... something to say?

247
00:19:22,318 --> 00:19:23,649
But you see...

248
00:19:24,353 --> 00:19:24,944
What?!

249
00:19:25,855 --> 00:19:29,416
But! But! But!
You said, Sensei!

250
00:19:29,926 --> 00:19:31,018
These guys...

251
00:19:31,761 --> 00:19:34,229
We're a three man squad, right?

252
00:19:35,531 --> 00:19:38,830
That's right!
The three of us are one, so!

253
00:19:41,037 --> 00:19:42,868
That's right! That's right!
That's right!

254
00:19:42,939 --> 00:19:44,531
That's right!

255
00:19:45,608 --> 00:19:47,667
The three of you are one, eh...

256
00:19:55,117 --> 00:19:56,345
You pass!

257
00:19:56,953 --> 00:19:57,385
What?!

258
00:19:57,887 --> 00:19:58,615
Whaaat?!

259
00:20:01,123 --> 00:20:02,249
You pass!

260
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:06,653
We passed?! Why?!

261
00:20:07,864 --> 00:20:09,354
You guys are the first.

262
00:20:10,099 --> 00:20:14,468
Up until now, it was always just dunces
who would meekly listen to what I said.

263
00:20:16,706 --> 00:20:19,072
A Ninja must see through deception...

264
00:20:19,942 --> 00:20:20,966
In the world of Ninja,

265
00:20:21,043 --> 00:20:24,012
those who break rules and codes
are branded as garbage...

266
00:20:25,114 --> 00:20:25,773
But...

267
00:20:27,350 --> 00:20:31,184
Those who don't cherish their friends are
garbage worse than that.

268
00:20:37,727 --> 00:20:41,663
He's... He's... kinda... cool...

269
00:20:42,899 --> 00:20:44,366
That's it for the exercise...

270
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:45,656
Everyone passes!

271
00:20:46,402 --> 00:20:48,927
Group Seven starts their mission
tomorrow!

272
00:20:49,939 --> 00:20:50,871
Yes, Sir!

273
00:20:53,809 --> 00:20:57,768
I did it!! I'm a Ninja!
Ninja! Ninja!

274
00:20:58,881 --> 00:20:59,677
Let's go home.

275
00:21:05,354 --> 00:21:06,844
Cha!

276
00:21:08,457 --> 00:21:08,980
I...

277
00:21:09,058 --> 00:21:12,152
knew this is how it'd turn out!

278
00:21:15,298 --> 00:21:18,131
Untie the rope!

279
00:22:52,845 --> 00:22:55,609
Oh, please! It'd been nothing but
blah missions until now.

280
00:22:55,681 --> 00:22:57,774
And just when I thought I'd finally
gotten an awesome mission,

281
00:22:57,850 --> 00:22:59,545
to think it'd be bodyguarding
this old man.

282
00:22:59,618 --> 00:23:02,746
He mocks the heck out of me,
calling me a brat.

283
00:23:02,821 --> 00:23:04,880
I'll tell him a thing or two.

284
00:23:04,957 --> 00:23:10,452
Someday I'll be...
Hey, are you listening?!

285
00:23:11,030 --> 00:23:14,295
Next episode: "A Dangerous Mission!
Journey to the Land of Waves!"

286
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:16,728
Don't miss me kick butt!
